Lua bindings to the EditorConfig C Core library.

Check http://editorconfig.org to see how to use EditorConfig.

NOTE: This project is *not* officially supported by EditorConfig in any way.

Build using cmake and place the resulting binary module somewhere in your LUA_CPATH.

To use in your Lua code:
  ec = require("editorconfig_core")
  print(ec._VERSION)
  t = ec.parse("/full/path/to/file")
  for _, k in ipairs(t) do print(string.format("%s = %s", k, t[k])) end
